Definition: a primitive root; to grave, by implication, to write (describe, inscribe, prescribe, subscribe); describe, record, prescribe, subscribe, write(-ing, -ten).
from {{h3787}}; success, advantage; equity, good, right.
from {{h3782}}; properly, a tottering, i.e. ruin; fall.

a primitive root; to totter or waver (through weakness of the legs, especially the ankle); by implication, to falter, stumble, faint or fall; bereave (from the margin), cast down, be decayed, (cause to) fail, (cause, make to) fall (down, -ing), feeble, be (the) ruin(-ed, of), (be) overthrown, (cause to) stumble, × utterly, be weak.
from {{h3782}}; properly, a feller, i.e. an axe; ax.
a primitive root; to grow fat (i.e. be covered with flesh); be covered. Compare {{h3680}}.
a primitive root properly, to be straight or right; by implication, to be acceptable; also to succeed or prosper; direct, be right, prosper.
from {{h3784}}; a magician; sorcerer.
from {{h3784}}; magic; sorcery, witchcraft.
a primitive root; properly, to whisper a spell, i.e. to inchant or practise magic; sorcerer, (use) witch(-craft).
perhaps from {{h3701}}; silvery; Casiphja, a place in Babylon; Casiphia.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h3701}}; money, silver.
from {{h3700}}; silver (from its pale color); by implication, money; money, price, silver(-ling).
a primitive root; to trouble; by implication, to grieve, rage, be indignant; be angry, be grieved, take indignation, provoke (to anger, unto wrath), have sorrow, vex, be wroth.
(Aramaic) or כְּעֶת; (Aramaic), feminine of {{h3705}}; thus (only in the formula 'and so forth'); at such a time.
(Aramaic) probably from {{h3652}}; now; now.
from {{h3680}}; a cushion or pillow (as covering a seat or bed); pillow.

from {{h3721}}; the hollow hand or palm (so of the paw of an animal, of the sole, and even of the bowl of a dish or sling, the handle of a bolt, the leaves of a palm-tree); figuratively, power; branch,   foot, hand((-ful), -dle, (-led)), hollow, middle, palm, paw, power, sole, spoon.
or (in Job) כַּעַשׂ; from {{h3707}}; vexation; anger, angry, grief, indignation, provocation, provoking, × sore, sorrow, spite, wrath.

or כִּתִּיִּי; patrial from an unused name denoting Cyprus (only in the plural); a Kittite or Cypriote; hence, an islander in general, i.e. the Greeks or Romans on the shores opposite Palestine; Chittim, Kittim.
from {{h3807}}; beaten, i.e. pure (oil); beaten.
from an unused root meaning to compact; a wall (as gathering inmates); wall.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h3796}}; wall.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h3789}}; write(-ten).
from {{h3789}}; something written, i.e. a writing, record or book; register, scripture, writing.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h3791}}; prescribing, writing(-ten).
from {{h3789}}; a letter or other mark branded on the skin; × any (mark).
from {{h3796}} and {{h376}}; wall of a man; Kithlish, a place in Palestine; Kithlish.
a primitive root; properly, to carve or engrave, i.e. (by implication) to inscribe indelibly; mark.
from {{h3717}}; a duplicate; double.
a primitive root; to bend; bend.
from an unused root meaning to connect; a girder; beam.
from {{h3722}}; a village (as covered in by walls); also a young lion (perhaps as covered with a mane); (young) lion, village. Compare {{h3723}}.
feminine of {{h3715}}; the village (always with the art.); Kephirah, a place in Palestine; Chephirah.
a primitive root; to fold together; figuratively, to repeat; double.
from {{h3721}}; a hollow rock; rock.
a primitive root; properly, to bend, i.e. (figuratively) to tame or subdue; pacify.
feminine of {{h3709}}; a leaf of a palmtree; branch.
from {{h3722}}; properly, a cover, i.e. (by implication) a tankard (or covered goblet); also white frost (as covering the ground); bason, hoar(-y) frost.
from {{h3799}}; properly, something carved out, i.e. ore; hence, gold (pure as originally mined); ((most) fine, pure) gold(-en wedge).
a primitive root; to dance (i.e. whirl); dance(-ing).
of foreign origin; byssus or fine vegetable wool; green.
patron from {{h3760}}; a Karmelite or inhabitant of Karmel (the town); Carmelite.
the same as {{h3759}}; Karmel, the name of a hill and of a town in Palestine; Carmel, fruitful (plentiful) field, (place).
of uncertain derivation; Keran, an aboriginal Idumaean; Cheran.
feminine of {{h3761}}; a Karmelitess or female inhabitant of Karmel; Carmelitess.
from {{h3697}}; to lay waste; waste.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h3678}}; a throne; throne.
from {{h3766}}; the leg (from the knee to the ankle) of men or locusts (only in the dual); leg.
a primitive root; to bend the knee; by implication, to sink, to prostrate; bow (down, self), bring down (low), cast down, couch, fall, feeble, kneeling, sink, smite (stoop) down, subdue, × very.

(occasionally with enclitic) כַּשְׂדִּימָה; towards the Kasdites into Chaldea), patronymically from {{h3777}} (only in the plural); a Kasdite, or descendant of Kesed; by implication, a Chaldaean (as if so descended); also an astrologer (as if proverbial of that people; Chaldeans, Chaldees, inhabitants of Chaldea.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h3778}}; a Chaldaean or inhabitant of Chaldaea; by implication, a Magian or professional astrologer; Chaldean.

a primitive root; to cut (off, down or asunder); by implication, to destroy or consume; specifically, to covenant (i.e. make an alliance or bargain, originally by cutting flesh and passing between the pieces); be chewed, be con-(feder-) ate, covenant, cut (down, off), destroy, fail, feller, be freed, hew (down), make a league (covenant), × lose, perish, × utterly, × want.
passive participle feminine of {{h3772}}; something cut, i.e. a hewn timber; beam.
by variation from {{h7164}}; the paunch or belly (as swelling out); belly.
of foreign origin; Karshena, a courtier of Xerxes; Carshena.
feminine of {{h3775}}; a young ewe; lamb.
from an unused root of uncertain meaning; Kesed, a relative of Abraham; Chesed.
probably from {{h3772}} in the sense of executioner; (compare {{h2876}}) (only collectively in the singular as plural); a Kerethite or life-guardsman; Cherethims, Cherethites.
apparently by transposition for {{h3532}}; a young sheep; lamb.
from {{h3772}}; a cut; Kerith, a brook of Palestine; Cherith.
perhaps an abridged plural of {{h3733}} in the sense of leader (of the flock); a life-guardsman; captains, Cherethites (from the margin).
(Aramaic) probably of Greek origin; to proclaim; make a proclamation.
(Aramaic) from {{h3745}}; a herald; herald.
the same as {{h3742}}; Kerub, a place in Babylon; Cherub.
of uncertain derivation; a cherub or imaginary figure; cherub, (plural) cherubims.
feminine of {{h3733}}; a meadow; cottage.
from {{h3739}}; a purchase; provision.
expanded from the same as {{h3522}}; a rim or top margin; compass.
from {{h3772}}; a cutting (of the matrimonial bond), i.e. divorce; divorce(-ment).
probably of foreign origin; the crocus; saffron.
of foreign derivation; Karkemish, a place in Syria; Carchemish.
of Persian origin; Karkas, a eunuch of Xerxes; Carcas.
from {{h3769}}; a dromedary (from its rapid motion as if dancing); swift beast.
from an unused root of uncertain meaning; a garden or vineyard; vines, (increase of the) vineyard(-s), vintage. See also {{h1021}}.
active participle of an imaginary denominative from {{h3754}}; a vinedresser; vine dresser (as one or two words).
from {{h3754}}; gardener; Karmi, the name of three Israelites; Carmi.
patronymically from {{h3756}}; a Karmite or descendant of Karmi; Carmites.
probably of foreign origin; carmine, a deep red; crimson.
from {{h3754}}; a planted field (garden, orchard, vineyard or park); by implication, garden produce; full (green) ears (of corn), fruitful field (place), plentiful (field).
from {{h3722}}; expiation (only in plural); atonement.

from {{h3722}}; properly, a cover, i.e. (literally) a village (as covered in); (specifically) bitumen (as used for coating), and the henna plant (as used for dyeing); figuratively, a redemption-price; bribe, camphire, pitch, ransom, satisfaction, sum of money, village.
from {{h3722}}; a lid (used only of the cover of the sacred Ark); mercy seat.
from {{h3723}} and {{h5984}}, with the article interposed; village of the Ammonite; Kefar-ha-Ammoni, a place in Palestine; Chefarhaamonai.
a primitive root; to curve; bow down (self).
from {{h3719}}; hunger (as making to stoop with emptiness and pain); famine.
from {{h3722}}; a village (as protected by walls); village. Compare {{h3715}}.

a primitive root; to cover (specifically with bitumen); figuratively, to expiate or condone, to placate or cancel; appease, make (an atonement, cleanse, disannul, forgive, be merciful, pacify, pardon, purge (away), put off, (make) reconcile(-liation).
(Aramaic) a root of uncertain correspondence; to fetter; bind.
a primitive root; to tread down; figuratively, to humiliate; cover.
from the same as {{h3525}}; to gird or clothe; clothed.
(Aramaic) from a verb corresponding to that of {{h3736}}; a mantle; hat.
from the same as {{h3564}}; properly, a deep round vessel, i.e. (specifically) a cor or measure for things dry; cor, measure. Aramaic the same.
(Aramaic) probably corresponding to {{h3738}} in the sense of piercing(figuratively); to grieve; be grieved.
patrial from {{h3731}}; a Caphtorite (collectively) or native of Caphtor; Caphthorim, Caphtorim(-s).

from {{h3769}} in the sense of plumpness; a ram (as full-grown and fat), including a battering-ram (as butting); hence, a meadow (as for sheep); also a pad or camel's saddle (as puffed out); captain, furniture, lamb, (large) pasture, ram. See also {{h1033}}, {{h3746}}.

or (Amos 9:1) כַּפְתּוֹר; probably from an unused root meaning to encircle; a chaplet; but used only in an architectonic sense, i.e. the capital of a column, or a wreath-like button or disk on the candelabrum; knop, (upper) lintel.
or (Amos 9:7) כַּפְתּוֹר; apparently the same as {{h3730}}; Caphtor (i.e. a wreath-shaped island), the original seat of the Philistines; Caphtor.
a primitive root; properly, to dig; figuratively, to plot; generally, to bore or open; dig, × make (a banquet), open.
usually assigned as a primitive root, but probably only a special application of {{h3738}} (through the common idea of planning implied in a bargain); to purchase; buy, prepare.
